race.description: Sky Racing Race Callers Cup Handicap (Bm70)
race.comment: BUENOS (7) returned to better form at Wagga, finishing strongly through the line after a disappointing Rosehill run two back. The rise to the mile looks ideal, and with McDougall taking over from a favourable draw, she gets the right run to deliver. ZIGGY ROSE (12) wasn't far away in a muddling affair at Hawkesbury last time, but her barnstorming win here two back remains fresh in the memory. Proven at the mile earlier in the prep, she gets blinkers on to sharpen her up and looks a genuine danger at the weights. LENNOX (6) resumes and the mile is a suitable starting point. No shock to see him grind into the finish. PETAWAWA (9) is rock-hard fit on the quick back-up and has peaks that measure up. Must be respected. DEVIL RIDER (4) may find the mile sharp, but if ridden positively he could sustain a strong effort.
